# WinUI Page UX Guidelines

Use these patterns for `RagnarokReconnectWinUI/Pages` files:

- Use Windows type ramp for hierarchy:
  - Page title: `TitleTextBlockStyle`
  - Section heading: `SubtitleTextBlockStyle` or `BodyStrongTextBlockStyle`
  - Metadata: `CaptionTextBlockStyle` + `TextFillColorSecondaryBrush`
- Keep strong grouping and spacing:
  - Explicit `Grid.RowDefinitions`
  - `Padding` ~16 and `RowSpacing` ~8-12
  - Visually separate dense rows with `Border` cards where readability is better than a raw table.
- Apply command basics:
  - Primary page actions near top
  - Context actions near section headers/content (`Refresh`, `Save`, `Copy`, `Test Send`).
- Apply content basics:
  - Prefer scannable labels and short summaries.
  - Use consistent terms: `Character`, `Status`, `Cause`, `Info`, `Time`.
  - Keep secondary/diagnostic detail in lower-contrast text.
- Avoid runtime UI injection for core layout controls; define structure directly in XAML.
- For logs, default to concise one-line entries and provide optional deep diagnostics.

## Example

```xaml
<TextBlock Style="{StaticResource TitleTextBlockStyle}" Text="Monitoring" />
<TextBlock Foreground="{ThemeResource TextFillColorSecondaryBrush}" Text="Live process health and alert toggles." />
<TextBlock Style="{StaticResource BodyStrongTextBlockStyle}" Text="Recent Incidents" />
```
